      "content": "that makes sense for the economic side of it, but i need to dig deeper into the more \"cultural\" justifications they used. like, were there arguments made about how segregation actually helped preserve different community identities or prevented \"social friction\"? i need to be able to represent that viewpoint as effectively as possible in the debate, so if you could flesh out the logic regarding how separation was framed as a way to maintain social order or cultural cohesion, that would be huge.",
